09/09/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- EBRD President Jean Lemierre praised the level of bilateral co-operation with Croatia and said that the Bank plans new investments of up to 200m euros in the country this year. Visiting Zagreb on Monday (8 September), he said the financing would go primarily to projects in tourism, urban infrastructure and local self-government. He also urged Croatian authorities to continue with reforms aimed at bringing the country closer to the EU. (HINA, BBC - 08/09/03)
